4. SOURCE CODE DISCLOSURE (NETWORK COPYLEFT)

If You run a Modified Version of the Software and allow third parties to interact with it through Network Use, You must:

a) Make the complete Corresponding Source of Your Modified Version available to all users who interact with the Software through the network;
b) Provide prominent notice to users explaining how they can obtain the Corresponding Source;
c) Make the source code available through one of the following methods:
   - A prominent link within the user interface or service
   - A publicly accessible version control repository (e.g., GitHub, GitLab)
   - A download link provided through the Software's interface or documentation
d) Ensure the source code remains available for at least 1 year from the last time You offered Network Use of the Modified Version;
e) License Your modifications under this License or a compatible license approved by PerfectDreams.

"Corresponding Source" means all the source code needed to generate, install, and run the Modified Version, including build scripts, configuration files, and installation instructions, but excluding:
- System libraries and general-purpose tools that are not part of the Software
- Proprietary third-party components that can be obtained separately

This requirement applies even if You are using the Software for Personal Use, as long as third parties can interact with it through a network.

EXEMPTIONS: This requirement does NOT apply if:
- You are running an unmodified version of the Software
- The Software is only accessible to You personally and no other users can interact with it
- You are testing modifications in a private, non-public environment

